        <h2 class="section-title h4">What it does</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          BirdNET-Analyzer applies BirdNET models to audio recordings to detect bird vocalizations and assign species
          labels. It supports both interactive use and scripted batch processing, making it suitable for everything from
          small pilot studies to multi-year monitoring projects.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-muted">
          <li>Processes single files or entire directories of recordings.</li>
          <li>Outputs detections with timestamps, species labels, and confidence scores.</li>
          <li>Supports geographic and temporal constraints for more realistic species lists.</li>
          <li>Provides a GUI and command-line workflows.</li>
        </ul>
